                                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="services_2" role="tabpanel">
                                        <div class="service-tab_details">
                                        <div class="service_details_heade">
                                        <h2>Aadhaar Enabled Payment System (AEPS)</h2>
                                        <div class="dmt_colms aeps_services_list">
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/fund_transfer.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Cash Deposit</h6></div>  
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/doorstep.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Cash Withdrawal</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Cost.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Balance Enquiry</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Digital.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Mini Statement</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/SMS-Alerts.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Aadhar to Aadhar Fund Transfer</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/SMS-Alerts.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Best finger Detection</h6></div>
                                        </div>
                                          <p class="mt-5">The Aadhaar Enabled Payment System (AEPS) is a banking service introduced by the Government of India to facilitate financial transactions using Aadhaar authentication. Aadhaar is a unique 12-digit identification number issued by the Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) to residents of India.</p>
                                          <p class="mt-1">AEPS allows individuals to access basic banking services such as cash withdrawal, balance inquiry, fund transfers, and other transactions using their Aadhaar number and biometric authentication, which can include fingerprints or iris scans. It eliminates the need for physical cards, documents, or signatures, making transactions more convenient and secure. The AEPS system is interoperable across different banks and service providers, enabling individuals to access their Aadhaar-linked bank accounts through any AEPS-enabled outlet or bank branch. It also facilitates the direct transfer of government benefits, subsidies, and pensions to beneficiaries' Aadhaar-linked bank accounts, ensuring timely and transparent disbursement of funds.</p>
                                       </div>
                                       <div class="feature_section_s">
                                       <div class="service_feature">
                                        <h3>Benifits</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                         <li>Access to Financial Services: AEPS enables individuals, especially those in rural and underserved areas, to access basic financial services such as cash withdrawals, balance inquiries, and fund transfers through Aadhaar authentication.</li>
                                         <li>Convenient Transactions: AEPS allows people to perform transactions using their Aadhaar number and biometric authentication, eliminating the need for physical cards or documents. This makes transactions more convenient and hassle-free.</li>
                                         <li>Financial Inclusion: AEPS plays a crucial role in promoting financial inclusion by bringing the unbanked and under banked population into the formal banking system. It allows them to perform banking transactions and avail themselves of various financial services.</li>
                                         <li>Government Benefit Disbursement: AEPS facilitates the direct transfer of government benefits, subsidies, and pensions to the beneficiaries' Aadhaar-linked bank accounts. This ensures timely and transparent disbursement of funds, eliminating intermediaries and reducing the risk of corruption.</li>
                                         <li>Secure Transactions: AEPS uses biometric authentication, such as fingerprints or iris scans, for secure identification and verification of individuals. This enhances the security of transactions, reducing the risk of fraud or identity theft.</li> 
                                         <li>Cost Savings: AEPS transactions are cost-effective compared to traditional payment methods. It eliminates the need for physical infrastructure, paperwork, and cash handling, resulting in cost savings for both individuals and service providers.</li>
                                         <li>Financial Empowerment: AEPS empowers individuals by giving them control over their financial transactions and reducing dependency on cash. It promotes digital payments, encourages savings, and provides access to credit and other financial products and services.</li>
                                         <li>Ease of Use: AEPS is user-friendly and accessible to people with minimal financial literacy. Its simple and intuitive interface makes it easy for individuals, including those from rural or remote areas, to perform transactions independently.</li>
                                         <li>Interoperability: AEPS is interoperable across multiple banks and service providers, allowing individuals to access their Aadhaar-linked accounts and perform transactions through any AEPS-enabled outlet or bank.</li>
                                         <li>Digital India Initiative: AEPS aligns with the vision of the Digital India initiative by promoting digital payments and driving financial inclusion. It contributes to building a less-cash economy and leveraging technology to empower individuals economically.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                       </div>
                                    
                                   </div>
                                       
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <!--3-->
                                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="services_3" role="tabpanel">
                                        <div class="service-tab_details">
                                        <div class="service_details_heade">
                                        <h2>Micro ATM (MATM)</h2>
                                        <div class="dmt_colms">
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/fund_transfer.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Get upto Rs.10 per Transaction</h6></div>  
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/doorstep.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>All Debit CardsAccepted</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Secure.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Safe And Secure</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Connection.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Easy Connection</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Technology.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Best Technology</h6></div>
                                        </div>
                                          <p class="mt-5">A Micro ATM (MATM) is a handheld device that functions as a mini-branch of a bank, allowing individuals to perform basic banking transactions in locations where traditional banking infrastructure is limited or inaccessible. It is a portable and compact version of an Automated Teller Machine (ATM) that brings banking services closer to the people, especially in rural and remote areas. Micro ATMs are equipped with features that enable individuals to carry out various banking activities, such as cash withdrawal, balance inquiry, fund transfers, and bill payments. These devices are typically operated by a business correspondent or agent of the bank, who acts as an intermediary between the bank and the customers.</p>
                                          <p class="mt-1">To use a Micro ATM, individuals can authenticate themselves using methods like their debit card, Aadhaar number, or biometric identification. The device connects to the bank's network and allows users to access their bank accounts and perform transactions securely.</p>
                                          <p class="mt-1">The primary purpose of Micro ATMs is to facilitate financial inclusion by extending banking services to underserved and unbanked populations. These devices eliminate the need for individuals to travel long distances to access banking services and provide a convenient and accessible alternative.</p>
                                          <p class="mt-1">Micro ATMs are typically battery-powered and equipped with features like a card reader, fingerprint scanner, keypad, and display screen. They are designed to be user-friendly and require minimal technical expertise to operate.</p>
                                       </div>
                                        <div class="feature_section_s">
                                       <div class="service_feature">
                                        <h3>Benifits</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                         <li>Financial Inclusion: Micro ATMs play a vital role in promoting financial inclusion by extending banking services to underserved and unbanked populations. They help individuals in remote and rural areas access basic banking facilities, thereby bridging the gap between banking services and people in need.</li>
                                         <li>Accessibility: Micro ATMs bring banking services closer to the people, eliminating the need to travel long distances to reach a bank branch or ATM. They are portable and can be operated by business correspondents or agents, enabling individuals to conduct transactions in their own localities.</li>
                                         <li>Convenience: MATMs provide individuals with the convenience of conducting various banking transactions, such as cash withdrawal, balance inquiry, fund transfers, and bill payments, without the need to visit a traditional bank branch. This saves time, effort, and transportation costs for users.</li>
                                         <li>Secure Transactions: Micro ATMs ensure secure transactions by employing authentication methods such as debit cards, Aadhaar numbers, or biometric identification (fingerprint scanning). These security measures help protect users' financial information and prevent unauthorized access to their accounts.</li>
                                         <li>Cost-Effective: Compared to setting up and maintaining traditional bank branches, Micro ATMs are a cost-effective alternative. They require lower infrastructure and operational costs, making it feasible for banks and financial institutions to extend their services to remote and economically underserved areas.</li>  
                                         <li>Revenue Generation: For business correspondents or agents operating the Micro ATMs, it serves as a source of income generation. They earn commission or fees for facilitating transactions and providing banking services to the local community, thereby creating employment opportunities.</li>
                                         <li>Technology Integration: Micro ATMs leverage technology to enable seamless transactions. They are equipped with features like card readers, fingerprint scanners, and display screens to provide a user-friendly interface for customers.</li>
                                         <li>Real-Time Transactions: Micro ATMs facilitate real-time transactions, allowing users to instantly withdraw cash or transfer funds. This helps individuals meet their immediate financial needs and access funds promptly.</li>
                                         <li>Banking Services on the Go: MATMs are portable devices that can be taken to different locations as per the demand for banking services. This flexibility enables banks to offer services at various events, fairs, or temporary setups, catering to the financial needs of diverse communities.</li>
                                         <li>Empowerment: Micro ATMs empower individuals by giving them control over their financial transactions. They enable people to access banking services, manage their accounts, and conduct transactions independently, promoting financial literacy and inclusion.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                       </div>
                                    
                                   </div>
                                       
                                       </div>
