                                    <!--4-->
                                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="services_4" role="tabpanel">
                                        <div class="service-tab_details">
                                        <div class="service_details_heade">
                                        <h2>QR ATM</h2>
                                        <p class="mt-1">QR ATM, also known as QR Code-enabled ATM, is a type of automated teller machine that allows users to initiate transactions by scanning a QR code using their Smartphone  or other mobile devices. It eliminates the need for physical cards and enables users to access banking services through a digital platform. With QR ATMs, users can scan a QR code displayed on the ATM screen using their mobile device's camera or a QR code scanning app. This initiates a connection between the user's mobile device and the ATM, enabling them to perform various transactions such as cash withdrawals, balance inquiries, fund transfers, and bill payments.</p>
                                          <p class="mt-1">The QR code contains information that identifies the transaction type and the user's account details. Once the QR code is scanned, the user can select the desired transaction on their mobile device, provide any necessary authentication such as a PIN or biometric verification, and confirm the transaction. The ATM processes the transaction and completes the requested operation accordingly.</p>
                                       </div>
                                       <div class="feature_section_s">
                                       <div class="service_feature">
                                        <h3>Benifits</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                         <li><Span style="color:red">Convenience:</Span> QR ATMs offer a convenient and user-friendly way to perform banking transactions. Users can simply scan a QR code using their Smartphone, eliminating the need for physical cards or additional authentication devices.</li>
                                         <li><Span style="color:red"> Contactless Transactions: </Span> QR ATMs promote contactless transactions, reducing the risk of transmitting germs or viruses, especially in situations like the COVID-19 pandemic. Users can complete transactions without physically touching the ATM or entering a PIN on a public keypad.</li>
                                         <li><Span style="color:red">Enhanced Security: </Span> QR ATMs employ robust security measures to protect user information and transactions. Encryption and authentication protocols ensure the integrity and confidentiality of data, reducing the risk of fraud or unauthorized access.</li>
                                          <li><Span style="color:red">Expanded Access: </Span> QR ATMs can be deployed in various locations beyond traditional bank branches, making banking services more accessible to users. They can be placed in remote areas, retail stores, or other convenient locations, providing financial services to individuals who may not have easy access to traditional banking infrastructure.</li>
                                           <li><Span style="color:red"> Reduced Costs:  </Span> QR ATMs can potentially reduce operational costs for banks and financial institutions. They require less physical infrastructure compared to traditional ATMs, such as card readers and PIN pads, resulting in lower maintenance and installation expenses.</li>
                                           <li><Span style="color:red"> Integration with Mobile Banking:</Span> QR ATMs often integrate with mobile banking applications, allowing users to seamlessly connect their banking accounts with their mobile devices. This integration enables a seamless and unified banking experience, empowering users to manage their finances efficiently.</li>
                                            <li><Span style="color:red">  Faster Transaction Processing: </Span> QR ATMs can streamline transaction processing, reducing the time required to complete banking operations. The scanning process and digital authentication can be faster than traditional card-based transactions, enhancing efficiency for users.</li>
                                             <li><Span style="color:red">Promotes Financial Inclusion: </Span> QR ATMs can contribute to financial inclusion by providing access to banking services for individuals who may not have bank accounts or traditional debit/credit cards. The convenience and availability of QR ATMs can help bridge the gap and extend financial services to underserved populations.</li>
                                              <li><Span style="color:red">Green Initiative: </Span> QR ATMs align with environmental sustainability efforts by reducing the need for physical cards and paper receipts. This promotes a paperless and eco-friendly approach to banking transactions.</li>
                                               <li><Span style="color:red">Innovation and Technological Advancement: </Span> QR ATMs represent a technological innovation in the banking industry, showcasing the integration of mobile devices, QR codes, and secure transaction processing. They demonstrate the commitment of financial institutions to embrace digital transformation and deliver modern banking experiences to their customers.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                       </div>
                                     
                                   </div>
                                       </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <!--5-->
                                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="services_5" role="tabpanel">
                                        <div class="service-tab_details">
                                        <div class="service_details_heade">
                                        <h2>Prepaid Card</h2>
                                        <div class="dmt_colms aeps_services_list">
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/movie-tickets.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Movie Tickets</h6></div> 
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/airline-tickets.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Airline Tickets</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Shopping.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Online Shopping</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/hotel.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Hotels</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/bill_payment.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Bill Payments</h6></div>
                                         <div><span class="dmt_icons"><img src="{site_url}skin/front-payol/images/service_icon/Railway.png" class="img-fluid"></span>
                                         <h6>Railway</h6></div>
                                        </div>
                                          <p class="mt-5">A prepaid card is a type of payment card that allows you to load a specific amount of money onto the card in advance. It is similar in appearance to a debit or credit card and can be used to make purchases or payments just like any other card. However, unlike traditional debit or credit cards that are linked to a bank account or credit line, a prepaid card is not directly tied to any account.</p>
                                         
                                       </div>
                                       <div class="feature_section_s">
                                       <div class="service_feature">
                                        <h3>Benifits</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                         <li><Span style="color:red">Convenience:</Span> Prepaid cards offer a convenient and accessible way to make payments. They can be used at various merchant locations, online stores, and ATMs, providing flexibility and ease of use.</li>
                                          <li><Span style="color:red">Financial Control: </Span> Prepaid cards allow you to control your spending and manage your budget effectively. Since you can only spend the amount loaded onto the card, it helps you avoid overspending and accumulating debt.</li>
                                           <li><Span style="color:red">Financial Inclusion: </Span> Prepaid cards promote financial inclusion by providing access to financial services for individuals who may be unbanked or under banked. They offer a viable alternative to traditional banking products and enable financial participation.</li>
                                            <li><Span style="color:red">Online and International Use:  </Span> Prepaid cards are widely accepted for online purchases, making them suitable for e-commerce transactions. Some prepaid cards can also be used internationally, allowing you to make payments or withdraw cash while traveling abroad.</li>
                                            <li><Span style="color:red">Budgeting and Goal Setting: </Span> Prepaid cards can be useful tools for budgeting and achieving financial goals. You can allocate specific amounts for different expenses or savings targets, helping you stay on track and manage your money effectively.</li>
                                              <li><Span style="color:red">Parental Control: </Span> Prepaid cards are often used as a means of providing financial independence and teaching financial responsibility to teenagers or young adults. Parents can load funds onto the card and monitor their child's spending, promoting responsible money management. Privacy Protection: Prepaid cards offer a level of privacy as they are not directly linked to your bank account. This can be beneficial for individuals who prefer to keep their financial transactions separate from their primary bank account.</li>
                                              
                                        </ul>
                                       </div>
                                     
                                   </div>
                                       
